51
00:02:04,810 --> 00:02:06,359
It was a primitive form of writing

52
00:02:06,359 --> 00:02:08,980
before the widespread use of computers.

53
00:02:08,980 --> 00:02:11,250
Anyway, the chips were small.

54
00:02:11,250 --> 00:02:14,020
But it turns out the size doesn’t of the
chip doesn’t matter.

55
00:02:14,020 --> 00:02:15,880
It’s how you use it.

56
00:02:15,880 --> 00:02:17,080
And according to Bloomberg,

57
00:02:17,080 --> 00:02:20,390
which cited 17 unnamed intelligence agents
and other sources

58
00:02:20,390 --> 00:02:22,430
within different tech companies,

59
00:02:22,430 --> 00:02:24,280
the Chinese Communist Party may have managed

60
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:26,810
to pull off the most sophisticated hack

61
00:02:26,810 --> 00:02:28,910
the world has ever seen.

62
00:02:28,910 --> 00:02:31,270
They allegedly installed these microchips

63
00:02:31,270 --> 00:02:34,140
on servers used by around 30 companies,

64
00:02:34,140 --> 00:02:36,140
including Amazon and Apple,

65
00:02:36,140 --> 00:02:38,830
as well as US government agencies.

66
00:02:38,830 --> 00:02:40,550
“[These] servers could be found in

67
00:02:40,550 --> 00:02:42,910
Department of Defense data centers,

68
00:02:42,910 --> 00:02:44,880
the CIA’s drone operations,

69
00:02:44,880 --> 00:02:48,200
and the onboard networks of Navy warships.”

70
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:50,310
The microchip would have given the Chinese
Communist Party

71
00:02:50,310 --> 00:02:54,060
secret access a huge number of these private
networks.

72
00:02:54,060 --> 00:02:55,060
Oops.

73
00:02:55,060 --> 00:02:58,510
So, how did the microchips get there?

74
00:02:58,510 --> 00:02:59,620
Well you see, there are essentially

75
00:02:59,620 --> 00:03:01,760
two ways to hack a computer.

76
00:03:01,760 --> 00:03:04,560
The most common kind is software hacking.

77
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:07,730
This is probably what you associate Chinese
hackers with.

78
00:03:07,730 --> 00:03:10,310
Like when they hacked the Office of Personnel
Management

79
00:03:10,310 --> 00:03:13,840
and stole data on over 22 million Americans.

80
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:15,780
Then there’s hardware hacking.

81
00:03:15,780 --> 00:03:17,310
That involves making physical changes

82
00:03:17,310 --> 00:03:19,880
or additions to the guts of computers—

83
00:03:19,880 --> 00:03:22,120
which builds in loopholes that can later be
exploited

84
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:24,290
by software hacking.

85
00:03:24,290 --> 00:03:26,990
Hardware hacking is really really hard to
do.

86
00:03:26,990 --> 00:03:28,930
According to one expert Bloomberg interviewed,

87
00:03:28,930 --> 00:03:32,960
“Having a well-done, nation-state-level
hardware implant surface

88
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:37,620
would be like witnessing a unicorn jumping
over a rainbow.

89
00:03:37,620 --> 00:03:39,320
Hardware is just so far off the radar,

90
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:42,010
it’s almost treated like black magic.”

91
00:03:42,010 --> 00:03:44,630
But while hard to pull off, if pulled off,

92
00:03:44,630 --> 00:03:47,540
it would give foreign agents major control
of

93
00:03:47,540 --> 00:03:50,230
critical computer infrastructure.

94
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:52,750
And it’s a little easier to pull off when
you’re the country

95
00:03:52,750 --> 00:03:56,070
that makes about 75% of the world’s mobile
phones

96
00:03:56,070 --> 00:03:58,480
and 90% of its PCs.

97
00:03:58,480 --> 00:04:01,220
Here’s what’s alleged to have happened.

98
00:04:01,220 --> 00:04:03,680
There’s a company called Elemental.

99
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:09,310
They make cubes that shoot other cubes with
lasers I guess?

100
00:04:09,310 --> 00:04:12,710
Actually they specialize in video processing
and storage.

101
00:04:12,710 --> 00:04:14,840
Their technology has been used for everything

102
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:17,280
from helping stream the Olympic Games,

103
00:04:17,280 --> 00:04:20,409
to communication with the International Space
Station,

104
00:04:20,409 --> 00:04:23,180
to even handling drone footage for the CIA.

105
00:04:23,180 --> 00:04:26,900
In 2015 Elemental was bought by Amazon.

106
00:04:26,900 --> 00:04:30,120
Wow, Amazon really does everything.

107
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:32,120
Elemental is an American company.

108
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:33,720
And their main product is assembled by

109
00:04:33,720 --> 00:04:35,840
another American company,

110
00:04:35,840 --> 00:04:37,870
Super Micro Computer Inc.

111
00:04:37,870 --> 00:04:41,840
They sell more server motherboards than almost
anyone else.

112
00:04:41,840 --> 00:04:43,889
One US intelligence official told Bloomberg,

113
00:04:43,889 --> 00:04:48,070
“Think of Supermicro as the Microsoft of
the hardware world.”

114
00:04:48,070 --> 00:04:50,430
So...like Microhard?

115
00:04:50,430 --> 00:04:53,810
No, forget that, it’s a terrible name.

116
00:04:53,810 --> 00:04:56,729
Anyway, it turns out, Supermicro’s core
product—

117
00:04:56,729 --> 00:04:57,889
their motherboards—

118
00:04:57,889 --> 00:05:01,099
are mostly made by contractors in China.

119
00:05:01,099 --> 00:05:03,930
So what seems to have happened is this:

120
00:05:03,930 --> 00:05:05,729
Agents for the People’s Liberation Army

121
00:05:05,729 --> 00:05:07,860
strolled into these contractors’ factories

122
00:05:07,860 --> 00:05:09,919
and offered some bribes to change

123
00:05:09,919 --> 00:05:12,759
the motherboard design ever so slightly.

124
00:05:12,759 --> 00:05:17,020
Just add this one teensy weensy little extra
microchip, ok?

125
00:05:17,020 --> 00:05:18,569
Of course, “If that didn’t work,

126
00:05:18,569 --> 00:05:19,949
they threatened factory managers

127
00:05:19,949 --> 00:05:23,069
with inspections that could shut down their
plants.”

128
00:05:23,069 --> 00:05:26,719
And while one tiny microchip sounds like it
can’t do a lot,

129
00:05:26,719 --> 00:05:28,449
it doesn’t have to.

130
00:05:28,449 --> 00:05:29,449
According to Bloomberg,

131
00:05:29,449 --> 00:05:32,689
“They were capable of doing two very important
things:

132
00:05:32,689 --> 00:05:33,940
telling the device to communicate

133
00:05:33,940 --> 00:05:36,069
with one of several anonymous computers

134
00:05:36,069 --> 00:05:38,120
elsewhere on the internet that were loaded
with

135
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:40,090
more complex code;

136
00:05:40,090 --> 00:05:42,499
and preparing the device’s operating system

137
00:05:42,499 --> 00:05:44,870
to accept this new code.”

138
00:05:44,870 --> 00:05:47,439
And this would give the Chinese military complete
access

139
00:05:47,439 --> 00:05:49,639
in a very hard to detect way.

140
00:05:49,639 --> 00:05:52,039
For example, they could make a secure machine

141
00:05:52,039 --> 00:05:54,259
not ask for a password.

142
00:05:54,259 --> 00:05:58,020
That way, hackers from China could just waltz
right in.

143
00:05:58,020 --> 00:05:59,020
Now for a long time,

144
00:05:59,020 --> 00:06:00,379
many Americans believed that China

145
00:06:00,379 --> 00:06:02,669
would never do something like this

146
00:06:02,669 --> 00:06:04,379
because it would jeopardize China’s place

147
00:06:04,379 --> 00:06:06,380
as the workshop of the world.

148
00:06:06,380 --> 00:06:08,830
And so everyone was happy being naïve,

149
00:06:08,830 --> 00:06:11,909
taking advantage of China’s low-cost manufacturing.

150
00:06:11,909 --> 00:06:14,879
Meanwhile, China continued to play a major
role

151
00:06:14,879 --> 00:06:17,529
building global computer infrastructure.

152
00:06:17,529 --> 00:06:21,150
And so companies became dependent on China.

153
00:06:21,150 --> 00:06:22,440
Oops.

154
00:06:22,440 --> 00:06:25,340
The fact that China has been a major state
sponsor

155
00:06:25,340 --> 00:06:28,279
of cyber espionage is nothing new.

156
00:06:28,279 --> 00:06:30,759
Back in 2015, there was even an agreement

157
00:06:30,759 --> 00:06:32,740
between Xi Jinping and President Obama

158
00:06:32,740 --> 00:06:36,810
that China would stop stealing US intellectual
property.

159
00:06:36,810 --> 00:06:37,919
That was the same year

160
00:06:37,919 --> 00:06:40,819
the Chinese microchips were first discovered.

161
00:06:40,819 --> 00:06:43,029
One official told Bloomberg that the White
House

162
00:06:43,029 --> 00:06:44,729
may have suspected at the time that

163
00:06:44,729 --> 00:06:47,349
“China was willing to offer this concession

164
00:06:47,349 --> 00:06:48,539
because it was already developing

165
00:06:48,539 --> 00:06:52,289
far more advanced and surreptitious forms
of hacking

166
00:06:52,289 --> 00:06:56,199
founded on its near monopoly of the technology
supply chain.”

167
00:06:56,199 --> 00:06:59,039
Not that the US government could do much about
it.

168
00:06:59,039 --> 00:07:01,249
Because it was the big American companies

169
00:07:01,249 --> 00:07:04,120
that were actually to blame for exposing themselves

170
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:06,139
to the China supply chain—

171
00:07:06,139 --> 00:07:08,470
and they refused to listen to the government’s
warnings.

172
00:07:08,470 --> 00:07:10,210
So it shouldn’t surprise you

173
00:07:10,210 --> 00:07:12,159
that both Apple and Amazon

174
00:07:12,159 --> 00:07:14,729
have denied the Bloomberg report.

175
00:07:14,729 --> 00:07:17,620
Except “The companies’ denials are countered

176
00:07:17,620 --> 00:07:22,110
by six current and former senior national
security officials.”

177
00:07:22,110 --> 00:07:24,689
In fact, not only did the companies know about
it—

178
00:07:24,689 --> 00:07:25,990
according to those officials—

179
00:07:25,990 --> 00:07:28,280
but Apple had reported their discovery of
it

180
00:07:28,280 --> 00:07:30,349
to the FBI in the first place,

181
00:07:30,349 --> 00:07:32,260
and Amazon went even further,

182
00:07:32,260 --> 00:07:35,970
by cooperating in a government investigation
about it.

183
00:07:35,970 --> 00:07:38,979
But of course, neither company said this to
the public.

184
00:07:38,979 --> 00:07:40,139
If it happened at all.

185
00:07:40,139 --> 00:07:43,009
Because, as I said, they totally deny it.

186
00:07:43,009 --> 00:07:46,169
Interestingly, “Apple did sever its relationship

187
00:07:46,169 --> 00:07:48,169
with Supermicro in 2016,

188
00:07:48,169 --> 00:07:51,159
